<font color="#FF0000">WHAT HAPPENED TO PTSD ? ?</font><br>
<tt>Thu Oct  2 20:35:39 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Observation: I have been quietly (a first for me) reading and learning from this site, but it has switched again. This was to be a site about PTSD, fact and fiction. Now it seems it is back to macho war stories again (yeah, I know you all will be pissed off at me for saying it).<br><br>
What happened to the seriousness of PTSD?  Am I the non smoking sign in a beer and cigar poker game?  (sorry?) It just seems to me, and to people who are knew, that we &quot;ought&quot; to stick to the thread's topic.  That is why I started the &quot;take it on back&quot; thread&quot;, so everyone could vent and piss and scratch and there was no other main reason.  <br><br>
I understand the important need for sharing war stories, but it is a two fold path.  One is a way to bond and build trust and intimacy. The other is a way to keep out outsiders, and to avoid intimacy and bonding by stopping at the guts and gore stage.  If you get stuck at the war story stage, you don't grow. The problem is that it feels so good.  <br><br>
Which path is this thread on?  Sorry to be such a bummer and rain on your parade, but I thought a position clarification was in order.<br><br>
Perhaps I couldn't stand sitting on my hands any longer.
